=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_FFT-Overview_ex12 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with complex oscillator character around 51 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with highpass character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: highpass
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 51.4651
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.0773
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5910
  pitch_clarity: 7.6351
  inharmonicity: 0.0383
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: 0.0264
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FFT Overview Example 12
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/FFT-Overview.html
// Tags: FFT-Overview, Guides, spectral
// ---
// --- Example 12 ---
chain = FFT(bufnum, { WhiteNoise.ar(0.2) }.dup);
